base_warranty_description: One-Year Manufacturer Limited Warranty
advanced_warranty_description:
Four-year extended warranty covers hardware failures
Battery covered for one year only
Individual user accidental damage to the device will be covered
Intentional damage, theft and mass-failure related to AoG events/disasters are not covered
Free shipping will be provided both to and from the repair depot
Dedicated Account Manager to ensure your repair needs are fully covered
Customer Central Repair Portal included to seamlessly track and request repairs
Device must either have a protective shell installed, or kept in a locking cart on the school district premises
Self-Maintainer Option - Warranty allows for the ability for the district to be a self-maintainer; i.e., repair devices themselves, or have the warranty provider service the device. In the event the district chooses to service the device, the vendor will provide parts as-needed to the district at no additional cost. Shipping of the replacement part and return shipping of the defective part will be paid for by the vendor. In the event the district opts to service the device, the vendor will provide servicing-time reimbursement in the form of either: A) in-house credit with the vendor, or B) payment to the school district; district's choice. Reimbursement or credit is in the amount of $15 per repair. Mechanical failures in the first year of the warranty do not qualify for the self-maintainer reimbursement, however, all other terms apply.
